begin_memory_text: I thought at first this was a young kid based on looks but was surprised how much high energy he had.
middle_memory_text: He was very high strung and took the majority of the conversation and I learned quite a few things in a world I thought was diversified.
end_memory_text: Very intelligent and living in one of the most densely populated areas of the U.S. and where politics are always influenced.
rest_of_day_open: I see it as well being a Friday evening and that my significant other and myself have plans on going to a theme park, it looks well! Plus working for a NFL team on Sunday is a perk too knowing I can see some of the game and purchase a few items at 50% off.
critical_positive: I learned something that in the world of orchestras that prejudice still lives to this day. If you are not Caucasian or Asian you are basically "written off" as the music world is dominated by both races.  It's sad to hear for an audition for the London Symphony Orchestra you have the perform behind a curtain.
critical_negative: The conversation went well but the person dominated the flow as I attempted to probe his life but didn't expect that he would go very much in-depth of where he is, how life is and what he plans on going.  The kid is very intelligent and see he will go into higher places

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and we spoke about what we study/work
middle_memory_text: We talked about his job then talked about the music world and how racist it really is.
end_memory_text: We started talking about my plans for the future since he was interested in my future since I am a double major. He wished me the best of luck, I wished him the best of luck, and we parted ways.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going pretty well. I have a project due on Monday and 3 homework's due by Sunday, but this conversation really made my entire week brighter.     It felt genuinely good to talk to a complete stranger about my plans since its been months since I have had a genuine good conversation with a random person.
critical_positive: I suppose our compatibility works very well, since we both come from similar cultures, we are used to being very warm and kind towards strangers and talking to them as if they were our friend. His willingness to listen to my plan is what really made this conversation work and the input he provided was very insightful.
critical_negative: The only thing that didn't work well was the occasional lag that occurred at random intervals for him. At one point he was cut off for a good 10-15 seconds worth and I had to improvise and think what did he actually say. Other than lag, everything worked just as intended.
